## Symbol Naming

`{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` lists exact symbol names. When a name ends with `@/`, it's a nyne namespace — nested symbols are **direct children** (no intermediate `symbols/` directory):

```
OVERVIEW shows: MyImpl@/  (Impl, with nested: process@/, validate@/)
Full path:      {{ paths.sym("file." ~ ext, "MyImpl@/process", ext) }}
```

- Top-level: `{{ paths.sym("", "my_function", ext) }}`
- Trait/interface impls: `{{ paths.sym("", "Display_for_Foo", ext) }}`
- Name collisions: `{{ paths.sym("", "Foo~Struct", ext) }}`, `{{ paths.sym("", "Foo~Fn", ext) }}`
- Nested (impl methods): `{{ paths.sym("", "Foo~Impl@/new", ext) }}`

When names are ambiguous, `ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/` shows the exact filesystem entries.
